 Towards the preparation for the on-going Nigerian Railway Modernization Project, the Lagos State Government has announced the closure of Akanni Doherty Street, Ashade from Friday, 28th to Sunday, 30th, June, 2019. The statement signed by the Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Transportation, Dr. Taiwo Olufemi Salaam stated that the closure is to allow the contractors of the project, CCECC and Devine Gate LTD, relocate and interconnect the700mm diameter public water main in the said vicinity. It explained further that the exercise will also involve excavation across the said road, as well as laying of High Density Polyethylene pipes, backfilling and compaction. Motorists and the general public are hereby urged to use alternative routes around the area to ensure a hitch free traffic. 